description: The Last West imagines a world in which all cultural and technological innovation has ground to a halt... and only one man knows why.

See behind the battlefield with this digital exclusive edition clocking in over 200 pages including never-before-seen extras featuring the script by Brian Michael Bendis and a variant cover gallery, plus layouts, inked pages, and color pages by David Marquez and Justin Ponsor!

This is the explosive first chapter in the comic event EVERYONE is talking about. A new Inhuman, with the ability to profile the future, emerges and the ramifications ripple into every corner of the Marvel Universe. Lines are drawn, bodies fall, and the Marvel Universe will be rocked to it's very core. The action starts here!

SOMEONE HAS MURDERED FORBUSH MAN! Could someone be targeting all of Marvel's funniest characters for death? That's what Deadpool thinks, and now he's gotta act before someone bumps off SQUIRREL GIRL, ROCKET RACCOON, GROOT, ANT-MAN, HOWARD THE DUCK and THE PUNISHER! (Like we said, the funny characters.) Good thing Deadpool is renowned for his investigative skills!

The Batgirls are back! A mysteriously cloaked shadow calling himself "The Reaper" is upset at the events that occurred last time with Harvey Dent, and is determined to nip the problem at its roots-Dr. Strange, Killer Frost, and the Penguin. Now the Batgirls must use their collective detective skills to warn those villains before the Reaper gets to them!
name: The Batgirls Fly by Night Part 1 of 3

description:
Operation Queen's Side

Captured by Pestarzt and his plague soldiers. Reynolds and the crew must do what they can to help save their friend Frank Kindle from the clutches of the evil madman.
name: Operation Queen's Side

description: Saved by Detective Kearnes from certain death at the end of the last issue, Ace is restrained as Gwen is taken captive. Now Ace must find a way to save his lesbian friend and convince the paramilitary fanatics that she is not a zombie like the others. Additionally, the Professor claims that Ace possesses the one thing that can end the lesbian zombie apocalypse for good; but Ace is unwilling to admit it. Will Ace and Gwen be able to escape the town and find help?

A bathtub full of corpses, a sister who won't accept that Wendy is anyone other than her best friend (Jennifer), and the realization that he may have acted a bit rashly all weigh heavily on Jason's psyche. And soul. Can Jason overlook the fact that three people are dead? And how can he be sure that he's not about to become yet another victim?
Erik Farrell finds himself at the mercy of the villainous Doctor Once. But, of course, Doctor Once has NO mercy!

Mirai and Mukaido have been lured into Metropoliman's trap. And while they have avoided perishing in the giant explosion, they aren't out of the woods yet. Can they take down their foe before he makes his next move? And what exactly is Metropoliman trying to accomplish...?
name: Chapter 10: Product of Coincidence

description: After narrowly escaping Wonder Woman (and the law) once before, Gault (actually his disembodied brain!) plots his revengeâ¦and seeks a new body to house his evil!
name: The Revenge of Gault's Brain Part 1 of 2

description: Before the FBI, before the X-Files, they were just two teenagers in search of the truth. On Martha's Vineyard, a young Fox Mulder investigates something strange happening on the island, while in San Diego, 13-year-old Dana Scully looks into the shocking murder of her teacher. Two kids, two mysteries, one conspiracy that threatens the future of humanity.
name: Chapter One
